fields.description:
{color:#333333}As a user i would like to be able to configure the fields of the "Single Issue" Jira Issue Link so that i can have shorter links inline with text that looks nice when for example the summary is long. This would be useful for example in tables with several column.
{color}

Basically, this is a duplicate of CONFSERVER-25966, I'm creating a new issue since I'm not sure whether someone will monitor the closed old issues. CONFSERVER-25966 was closed because "{color:#333333}I really wouldn't want to making it more complicated by having settings as to how it displayed, so we don't have any plans to make this change.{color}" As of now, there is already a configuration GUI for this links but it's mainly for Tables and not for Single Issues. Therefore, IMHO the previous reason for closing this no longer applies.

*Description:*

AJS.$('#labels-section') resolves to AJS.$(' (None) -section') when used in Main Layout template causing the selector to fail during execution.

 

*To Reproduce:* 
 Add the following code

 
{code:java}
#if ($userAccessor.hasMembership('confluence-users', $helper.action.remoteUser.name))
#else
    <script type="text/javascript">
    AJS.toInit(function(){                   
       AJS.$('#labels-section').hide(); 
    });
</script>
#end
{code}
to Main layout template just after </html> tag. Debug on page refresh and notice "#labels" has been replaced with "(None)".

*Expected:*

Selector resolves to #labels

 

*Actual:*

Selector resolves to (None)

 

*Temporary workaround:*
Replace
{code:java}
AJS.$('#labels-section').hide()
{code}
with
{code:java}
document.getElementById("labels-section").style.display = "none";{code}
Link to Community post:

[https://community.atlassian.com/t5/Confluence-questions/After-upgrade-to-6-7-hiding-certain-selectors-doesn-t-work/qaq-p/726448#M97766]
